and I had to dress
some of the most beautiful
women in the world

984
00:49:41,079 --> 00:49:43,179
with some of the handsomest
men in the world.

985
00:49:43,181 --> 00:49:45,514
So I figured I'd better go
to the most important

986
00:49:45,516 --> 00:49:47,616
jewelry company
in the world.

987
00:49:47,618 --> 00:49:51,120
When a person puts on
a great piece of jewelry,

988
00:49:51,122 --> 00:49:53,689
and a Tiffany jewelry,
they feel a certain way.

989
00:49:53,691 --> 00:49:55,358
It gives them a certain
joie de vivre

990
00:49:55,360 --> 00:49:57,693
that they don't--might not
have without that.

991
00:49:57,695 --> 00:50:00,029
I mean, Julia has it
either way.

992
00:50:00,031 --> 00:50:02,031
But it makes her feel good,

993
00:50:02,033 --> 00:50:04,700
makes her feel like she has
something important on,
which she does.

994
00:50:04,702 --> 00:50:08,170
With movie stars
like Julia Roberts
and so on and so forth,

995
00:50:08,172 --> 00:50:11,574
I don't say, "wear this,
and wear it now!"

996
00:50:11,576 --> 00:50:13,242
I sit down with them
and I say,

997
00:50:13,244 --> 00:50:14,777
"this is jewelry
from Tiffany's.

998
00:50:14,779 --> 00:50:17,680
Take a look at it and see
what catches your eye,

999
00:50:17,682 --> 00:50:19,382
see what you enjoy."

1000
00:50:19,384 --> 00:50:21,250
And then they find things
that they like

1001
00:50:21,252 --> 00:50:23,085
and they try 'em on.

1002
00:50:23,087 --> 00:50:25,054
And they try 'em on
with the dress they're wearing

1003
00:50:25,056 --> 00:50:26,455
and they try 'em on again
and again and again.

1004
00:50:26,457 --> 00:50:28,724
And they change their mind
four, five times.

1005
00:50:28,726 --> 00:50:32,661
So... and then they finally
settle in on a piece.

1006
00:50:32,663 --> 00:50:34,730
You are up to something,
Danny. What?

1007
00:50:34,732 --> 00:50:36,399
And don't say
"you came here for me."

1008
00:50:36,401 --> 00:50:37,733
You're pulling a job,
aren't you?

1009
00:50:37,735 --> 00:50:40,403
Well, know this.
No matter what it is,

1010
00:50:40,405 --> 00:50:42,738
you won't win me back.

1011
00:50:42,740 --> 00:50:45,207
Tess, I just came
to say goodbye.

1012
00:50:45,209 --> 00:50:47,276
I got you something,
and, um--

1013
00:50:47,278 --> 00:50:48,744
-aw, it's a Tiffany box.
-Thank you, yeah.

1014
00:50:48,746 --> 00:50:51,414
I wasn't--i wasn't invited
to the wedding.

1015
00:50:51,416 --> 00:50:53,749
--No.

1016
00:50:53,751 --> 00:50:55,418
Yeah, we don't know
each other.

1017
00:50:55,420 --> 00:50:57,420
Not well enough for you
to come to the wedding, no.

1018
00:50:57,422 --> 00:50:59,422
--It would've been really odd.

1019
00:50:59,424 --> 00:51:01,824
I know I don't know you,
but I just wanted

1020
00:51:01,826 --> 00:51:04,093
-to give you something.
