made about New York.

1157
01:00:48,178 --> 01:00:52,147
Every possible building,
statue, has been in a movie.

1158
01:00:52,149 --> 01:00:53,882
This has never been
in a movie.

1159
01:00:53,884 --> 01:00:55,250
That's how I convinced
Marty to do it.

1160
01:00:55,252 --> 01:00:57,853
It's so beautiful,
that clock,

1161
01:00:57,855 --> 01:01:00,322
that from the back
that clock is beautiful.

1162
01:01:00,324 --> 01:01:02,124
And people, you know,
don't really see

1163
01:01:02,126 --> 01:01:03,358
the clock
that I came out of

1164
01:01:03,360 --> 01:01:05,761
because you can only see it

1165
01:01:05,763 --> 01:01:07,863
if you're going
up park Avenue.

1166
01:01:07,865 --> 01:01:11,133
Our Tiffany clock,
all the original parts
are still there.

1167
01:01:11,135 --> 01:01:13,035
The original motors,
the original gears.

1168
01:01:13,037 --> 01:01:15,704
With all these pieces
a hundred years old,

1169
01:01:15,706 --> 01:01:18,206
it's accurate
to within one second

1170
01:01:18,208 --> 01:01:21,977
every 1,400,000 years.

1171
01:01:37,226 --> 01:01:39,261
Well, I can say
that I was thrilled

1172
01:01:39,263 --> 01:01:42,931
to read the biography
of Steve Jobs

1173
01:01:42,933 --> 01:01:45,400
because I had not realized
that Steve Jobs

1174
01:01:45,402 --> 01:01:49,738
had appreciated the design
and the work of Louis Tiffany.

1175
01:01:49,740 --> 01:01:51,339
One of the illustrations
in that book,

1176
01:01:51,341 --> 01:01:54,076
it depicted Steve Jobs
sitting on the floor

1177
01:01:54,078 --> 01:01:56,411
in a virtually empty
room in his home

1178
01:01:56,413 --> 01:01:59,414
where the only object
was a floor lamp.

1179
01:01:59,416 --> 01:02:00,916
What the book
went on to say

1180
01:02:00,918 --> 01:02:02,851
is that he couldn't
furnish his home

1181
01:02:02,853 --> 01:02:05,787
because he couldn't find
anything that met his standards

1182
01:02:05,789 --> 01:02:07,222
and there you have
a Tiffany lamp.

1183
01:02:18,000 --> 01:02:20,001
He appreciated
the beauty in it
and the cleanl--

1184
01:02:20,003 --> 01:02:21,436
what he was
trying to say.

1185
01:02:21,438 --> 01:02:24,506
Well, Tiffany was about
beauty, and he was too.

1186
01:02:24,508 --> 01:02:27,776
It was about design-- and
perfect design.

1187
01:02:27,778 --> 01:02:29,377
When you think
of the magnolia,

1188
01:02:29,379 --> 01:02:31,279
you harken back
to nature.

1189
01:02:31,281 --> 01:02:32,447
And then,
even if you go further,

1190
01:02:32,449 --> 01:02:34,116
you think
of Japanese culture

1191
01:02:34,118 --> 01:02:36,118
because Tiffany
travelled tremendously

1192
01:02:36,120 --> 01:02:37,786
throughout the world
and he brought

1193
01:02:37,788 --> 01:02:40,122
many of his influences
from traveling

1194
01:02:40,124 --> 01:02:42,124
into his design aesthetic.

1195
01:02:42,126 --> 01:02:45,026
So you can relate to it
in very different ways.

1196
01:02:45,028 --> 01:02:47,796
One of his quotes was
"nature is always beautiful."

1197
01:02:47,798 --> 01:02:50,031
I think that
was very inspirational.

1198
01:02:50,033 --> 01:02:52,367
Color was
so important to him.

1199
01:02:52,369 --> 01:02:54,870
He was--he considered
himself a colorist

1200
01:02:54,872 --> 01:02:58,507
and it comes through
in everything that was made.

1201
01:03:10,820 --> 01:03:13,255
By the time that
Charles Lewis Tiffany dies,

1202
01:03:13,257 --> 01:03:16,825
Louis has really mastered
all of these different forms.

1203
01:03:16,827 --> 01:03:18,160
And I think that
the jewelry really

1204
01:03:18,162 --> 01:03:20,328
is such a continuation
of his aesthetic.

1205
01:03:20,330 --> 01:03:22,831
Again, the emphasis on color.

1206
01:03:22,833 --> 01:03:24,833
The emphasis on nature.

1207
01:03:24,835 --> 01:03:28,003
Louis went on to do
very much the same
as his father did,

1208
01:03:28,005 --> 01:03:29,871
which was to create a brand

1209
01:03:29,873 --> 01:03:34,009
and to open this
incredible luxury, sort of,
retail emporium,

1210
01:03:34,011 --> 01:03:37,345
and very much followed
in his father's footsteps.

1211
01:03:48,858 --> 01:03:50,559
The sidewalks
along fifth Avenue

